  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d3242afaaaaf14638771958b6dbf1ceeaff5e974" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:14.133ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle E_{1},E_{2},E_{3},\ldots }"></span> are measurable sets that are decreasing (meaning that <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle E_{1}\supseteq E_{2}\supseteq E_{3}\supseteq \ldots }">
  <semantics>
